  "texts": [
    "It takes super-resolution reconstructed images as input and combines them with the SASE module, the SPP module, and a multilevel sensory field structure.",
    "They also adjust the Number of detection output layers through feature weight exploration to improve the feature utilization efficiency.In summary, high-resolution object detection can benefit from applying SR to the input image to improve the performance of deep learning-based object detection algorithms on low-resolution images.",
    "This is especially important for small objects or low-resolution images in traffic scenes to further improve detection accuracy and speed.",
    "Loss function optimizationOptimizing loss functions is one of the effective strategies for improving object detection performance.",
    "In complex traffic scenes, where there may be class imbalances in some datasets, optimizing loss functions can help the model focus more on minority classes, thus enhancing performance."
  ]
